      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">32.703-3</ph> Contracts crossing fiscal years.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2134e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2159e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            A contract that is funded by annual appropriations may not cross fiscal years, except in accordance with statutory authorization (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.,</i>
                  <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section6302&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">41 U.S.C.6302</xref>, <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title31-section1308&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">31 U.S.C.1308</xref>, <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title42-section2459a&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">42 U.S.C. 2459a</xref>, <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title42-section3515&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">42 U.S.C.3515</xref>, and paragraph (b) of this subsection), or when the contract calls for an end product that cannot feasibly be subdivided for separate performance in each fiscal year (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.,</i> contracts for expert or consultant services).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2159e33">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> The head of an executive agency, except NASA, may enter into a contract, exercise an option, or place an order under a contract for severable services for a period that begins in one fiscal year and ends in the next fiscal year if the period of the contract awarded, option exercised, or order placed does not exceed oneyear (<xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3133&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external">10 U.S.C. 3133</xref>
                     
                   and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section3902&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">41 U.S.C. 3902</xref>). Funds made available for a fiscal year may be obligated for the total amount of an action entered into under this authority.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
